        Avul Pakir Jainulabdeen Abdul Kalam (1931â€“2015) was an Indian aerospace scientist and the 11th President of India. Known as the Missile Man, he played a pivotal role in India's civilian space and missile programs. He was deeply loved for his humility, patriotism, and dedication to inspiring youth.
      </p>
      <p>
        His work in India's nuclear and space programs helped shape modern India. Despite his scientific achievements, he remained a teacher at heart, dedicating his life to education and youth empowerment.
